To compare the predictions with the actual prices in y_Val, the best method is to use scatter plot

In [174]:
plt.scatter(y_val, predictions)
Out[174]:
<matplotlib.collections.PathCollection at 0x10c62d3df08>

The results line up in the figure above which means that the predictions and the real values are almost equal.

Let's make a histogram to show the residuals which is the difference between the actual values and the predicted values

In [175]:
sns.distplot((y_val-predictions))
Out[175]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x10c6358ad48>

if the histogram shows a normal distribution, it means that linear regression was a good choice to use with this data.
